A ministerial meeting of Africa's lumber producers will convene in Angola to discuss new policies for imports and exports.
The African Timber Organization, comprising 13 member states, will focus on timber industry development and rainforest conservation.
In China, efforts are underway to protect black gibbons in Hainan province and expand the Xishuangbanna rainforest reserve.
Malaysia and Austria aim to enhance bilateral relations, while Brazil and Malaysia plan to launch remote sensing satellites to monitor tropical forests.
Tanzania's Vice-President calls for cooperation to combat deforestation, emphasizing the importance of sustainable practices and technological advancements.
